<h1>Fees & Funding</h1>
<hr>
<p>Fees and Funding

The total course fee for the Ultrasound Training Program is structured into two distinct components, corresponding to the academic and practical phases of the program. This phased fee structure allows students to clearly understand the costs associated with each stage of training.
<br>
<hr>
1. Online Theory Training – AUD 20,000<br>

This fee covers the complete academic component of the program and includes:<br>
  •  Access to the online learning management system (LMS)<br>
  •  Virtual classroom lectures delivered by qualified faculty<br>
  •  Structured, module-wise curriculum<br>
  •  Digital study materials and academic resources<br>
  •  Ongoing coursework, assignments, and assessments<br>
  •  Academic guidance and student support during the theory phase<br>

The online theory component must be successfully completed before progression to the hands-on practical training phase.<br>
<hr>

2. Hands-On Practical Training – AUD 16,000<br>

The practical training component is designed to provide real-world clinical exposure and applied learning.<br>
  •  A scholarship of AUD 6,000 will be granted towards this component, subject to Academy policies, satisfactory academic performance, and progression eligibility.<br>
    This component includes:<br>
  •  Supervised hands-on ultrasound training<br>
  •  Practical assessments and evaluations<br>
  •  Applicable examination fees related to the practical phase<br>
  •  Course completion and training documentation<br>

The location of hands-on training will be decided by the Academy and may be conducted overseas, in accordance with program requirements.
<br>

Additional Costs (Not Included)<br>
<hr>
The following expenses are not included in the course fees and must be borne separately by the student, where applicable:<br>
  •  Graduation ceremonies and related functions<br>
  •  Event participation fees, gowns, certificates, or celebratory activities<br>
  •  Travel, accommodation, food, insurance, and personal expenses<br>
  •  Visa and immigration-related costs for overseas training<br>

<hr>
Payment & Policy Notes<br>
  •  All fees are payable as per the prescribed payment schedule.<br>
  •  Course fees are subject to the Academy's Terms & Conditions, refund policy, and withdrawal policy.<br>
  •  Progression from the theory phase to the practical phase is conditional upon successful completion of required modules and assessments.
<br>
This transparent fee structure ensures students clearly understand their financial commitment at each stage of the program before enrolment</p>

